    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"manageable compared to fossil fuels\" feels like a bit of a loaded way to put it. shouldn't we be looking at the actual lifecycle for both? like, if you look at the total carbon footprint and the damage to local ecosystems, isn't it more accurate to say wind is just a different kind of impact rather than \"cleaner\"?",
